# GitHub Push Guide — Online Retail Dashboard

## Prerequisites
- Git installed → check with `git --version`
- GitHub account at github.com
- Your project folder ready with all files

---

## Step 1 — Create the Repository on GitHub

1. Go to [github.com](https://github.com) and log in
2. Click the **+** icon (top right) → **New repository**
3. Fill in:
   - **Repository name:** `online-retail-dashboard`
   - **Description:** `Interactive sales dashboard built with Python, Pandas, Plotly & Streamlit`
   - **Visibility:** Public
   - ❌ Do NOT check "Add a README" (you already have one)
4. Click **Create repository**
5. Copy the repo URL — looks like:
   `https://github.com/rcrahul0001-web/online-retail-dashboard.git`

---

## Step 2 — Create a .gitignore File

Create a file named `.gitignore` in your project folder with this content:

```
# Cleaned data (auto-generated by data_audit.py)
data/clean/

# Python cache
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.env

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Streamlit cache
.streamlit/
```

This prevents the cleaned CSV and junk files from being uploaded.

---

